Vienna architect Karl Mang 92 @-@ year @-@ old deceased
Karl Mang , one of the doyens of Vienna &apos;s architecture , is dead .
he died as early as September 5 at the age of 92 , according to the artist &apos;s house on Tuesday .
with Mang , the artist &apos;s house loses an honorary member and at the same time &quot; one of the most important architects of the second half of the 20th century in Vienna , &quot; as stated in the broadcast .
born in Vienna in 1922 , Mang studied architecture at the Technical University in Vienna near Friedrich Lehmann during and after World War II .
he worked as a freelance architect since 1952 , but also worked as a teacher , writer and institute manager .
from 1972 to 1983 he was president of the Austrian Institute of Formation .
in the 1980s , he was charged with setting up the treasury office in Vienna &apos;s Hofburg and reconstructing the Palais Lobkowitz into the Austrian theatre museum .
