Croatian police were able to pick them up in nearby corn fields .
according to local media , police vehicles with new refugees have been constantly arriving in Croatia &apos;s Tovarnik region since then .
they are mainly Syrians and Afghans , including many women and children .
emergency services and the Red Cross are already in use .
in the coming days , his country is counting around 4000 refugees , Interior Minister Ranko Ostojic said .
moreover , buses from Presevo on the Macedonian @-@ Serbian border , which had so far brought migrants to the Hungarian border , would be diverted towards Croatia , Croatian and Serbian media reported on Wednesday .
the government in Belgrade denied , however , that it was to suggest to the people that certain routes should be taken : &quot; neither can we , nor do we , &quot; it said .
