about Croatia , Slovenia and Austria to Germany
the inmates had been travelling all night from Serbia &apos;s roughly 500 @-@ kilometer Macedonian border .
&quot; we have heard that Hungary has done so , so the police have told us that we should go here , &quot; said one of the refugees .
they wanted to travel further through Croatia , Slovenia and Austria .
this could actually lead to the postponement of the previous Balkan route Turkey @-@ Greece @-@ Macedonia @-@ Serbia @-@ Hungary , already predicted by observers .
Croatia : &quot; comprehensive border control options &quot;
Croatia &apos;s Interior Minister Ostojic had previously stressed that his country had prepared plans for possible exceptional situations in the event of a strong influx of refugees .
he did not mention details , but he pointed out that Croatia as a non @-@ Schengen member has &quot; comprehensive border control capabilities . &quot;
strict controls are carried out to qualify for membership of the Schengen area .
Slovenia has been part of this since 2007 , and the EU &apos;s partners have been consistently reporting to the country on the standard of border controls .
on the Serbian side , some 300 refugees remain stuck behind the Hungarian border fence .
