according to the Hungarian authorities , the two border crossings of Horgos and Backi Breg remain completely closed .
whether the remaining refugees want to travel to the Croatian border is still unclear .
Serbian Interior Minister Nebojsa Stefanovic tried to calm down Wednesday morning at a local show in Horgos : he considers the debates on alternative routes of refugees to be premature after the Hungarian border is now closed .
it would not be very high numbers of refugees at the moment .
it is not yet possible to say whether they would continue their journey through Hungary , Croatia or any other country .
aid workers advise migrants to - dangerous - alternative routes
however , private Hungarian refugee workers have already begun distributing maps to refugees on which alternative routes are drawn through Croatia .
however , the border crossing between Serbia and Croatia is not undangerous : in parts of the border area , there are still uncovered mines 20 years after the end of the Croatian war .
on Wednesday afternoon , Croatian police announced that a team of miners was sent to the border region .
