Hoyerswerda : small life aid for refugees
more and more refugees arrive in Germany these days .
to give you a warm welcome does not go without the commitment of countless volunteers .
in Hoyerswerda , too , there are a number of people who support unselfish asylum seekers in the city .
they include Petra and Klaus Heine .
Petra Heine is a teacher with a body and soul .
she is also happy to teach her 74 runs .
every Thursday , she does it in the asylum seeker &apos;s home on Dillinger Street .
it helps refugees from Syria , Kurdistan , Kosovo and Pakistan to learn the German language .
of course , this is quite different from a school .
Brazil &apos;s paediatric company Rio Grande promotes nutrition for healthy breastfeeding
the Brazilian paediatric organization SPRS is trying , in a shocking way , to educate women about the importance of good nutrition during breast @-@ feeding .
breast milk consists of a variety of proteins , fats , vitamins and carbohydrates that give babies all the nutrients they need to build a strong immune system .
due to the additional energy requirements , pregnant women and young mothers are advised to increase their daily calorie intake by about 500 calories a day .
however , new research suggests that higher calorie intake is not the only dietary adjustment mothers should make .
a recent study led by Robert Waterland , a professor at Baylor College of Medicine in Texas , showed that a healthy diet of pregnant women actually affects the genes of their babies and protects them from the development of tumors .
unfortunately , an unhealthy diet of the child can negatively affect the immune system .
