&quot; no , that &apos;s so agreed , &quot; she explained .
on the question of an agreement under which Germany could host a certain number of refugees from Austria per day , Mikl @-@ Leitner said there had already been discussions on this between the Director @-@ General for Public Security and representatives of Germany .
she did not mention specific figures and pointed to talks Wednesday in Berlin .
in recent days , tens of thousands of refugees have come to Austria via the so @-@ called Balkan route .
their goal is mostly Germany .
Chancellor Angela Merkel ( CDU ) and her Austrian colleague Werner Faymann , together with several other EU leaders , requested a special summit next week .
Germany had begun temporary border controls on Sunday .
EU countries have so far failed to agree on a common approach to the crisis .
EU Home Affairs Ministers intend to take a new approach to the mandatory distribution of a further 120 000 refugees at a special meeting next Tuesday ( 22 September ) .
in view of the strong refugee vessel in Germany , the federal government wants to give more support to countries in the initial reception and distribution of people .
the federal government will manage this together with the countries , Merkel announced late Tuesday night after almost four @-@ month consultations with the prime ministers at the chancellor &apos;s office in Berlin .
Merkel stressed that those people who needed protection also complained .
but those who do not have a lead perspective cannot remain in Germany .
this view was strongly shared in the round .
the Chancellor stressed that the state as a whole must now cope with a &quot; huge effort . &quot;
thousands of desperate refugees are now stuck on the Balkans route .
Hungary closed its 175 kilometres long border with Serbia on the night of Tuesday .
a few hours later , the government in Budapest announced that the border with Romania would also disappear with a fence .
this neighbouring country is different from Serbia to the EU .
Hungary wants to prevent smugglers from seeking escape routes over Romania , Hungary &apos;s Foreign Minister Peter Szijjarto said on the planned new border fence .
the Romanian government immediately condemned the plan .
there were initial arrests of people who had average the fence .
in Turkey , meanwhile , eyewitness reports showed thousands more migrants heading to the Greek border .
