no diet fruit - Mangos contain a lot of sugar
Mangos are exotic and juicy @-@ sweet .
but those who want to pay attention to his slim line are often more likely to get away from them .
because mangos contain relatively much sugar - especially Saccharose .
healthy are the exotic fruits anyway : in them , B vitamins , vitamins E and C. above all , Mangos contain a lot of vitamin A and its pre @-@ stage beta cararotin .
those who eat the fruits thus support vision , immune system and metabolic processes in the body .
when buying Mangos should not be too soft or too firm and smell pleasant .
the shaft color alone says nothing about how ripe the fruit is - so green mangos can also taste very delicious .
they should be stored at room temperature and consumed within days .
then , of course , they taste pure or sweet food .
but a mango also gives hearty dishes a special touch .
it mitigates the slightly bitter taste of some leaf salads like Chicoree and Radiccio .
and a mangochutney fits well with fish , poultry , lamb and venison .
