this is where rain takes hold until Thursday night .
in sum , in the next 48 hours south of the Alps , there will have to be more than 100 litres of rain per square metre , having fallen in recent days .
on Thursday morning , the Föhn takes off the air , in the wake of a cold front with strong , partially trite rain from West to East over Switzerland .
along with the cold front , the wind is fresh strongly to stormy , and temperatures are falling significantly .
