XI urges to open the economy wider for the world
the economy needs to open wider to the outside to promote growth , President Xi Jinping said Tuesday of a group charged with steering reform .
&quot; China should strive to attract foreign investment and know @-@ how and improve strategies for business start @-@ ups , &quot; he said in a speech at the 16th meeting of the Central Leader Group for deepening comprehensive reform .
promoting new start @-@ ups and advancing reforms will bring new momentum and vitality and provide new space for economic growth , Xi said .
the governing group has adopted a number of directives , including a negative list on market access rules , relaxation of border control policies , promotion of state enterprises ( SOE ) , private capital , and overhaul of the population reporting system .
according to the statement , a negative list is being drawn up identifying sectors and companies that are not eligible for investment .
the system is gradually tested and improved by testing programs .
the initiative is important as it gives the market a greater role in the allocation of resources , guarantees a legal business environment and makes the market more open , the statement said .
the government will also ease controls on the powers conferred on businesses and ensure companies decide how to conduct their business .
the statement also said China will allow border areas to explore new models of cross @-@ border economic cooperation and new mechanisms to promote regional growth .
other areas of private investment will be opened up as part of an offer to open state @-@ controlled sectors .
&quot; the government will not change its policy toward foreign investment and will protect the legitimate interests of leveraged companies and provide better services to them , &quot; the statement said .
in addition , it is made easier for foreigners to apply for permanent residence permits or the Green Card by optimising requirements and facilitating the application process .
the right of lawyers to guarantee their activities and to employ professional judges and prosecutors was also discussed at a meeting .
the meeting also included Premier Li Keqiang and key leaders such as Liu Yunshan and Zhang Gaoli , as reported in a statement released after the meeting .
EU seeks to double mercury limit value in predators
the European Commission wants to double the limit values for mercury in large predators , thereby encouraging consumers to have a much higher dose of nervous energy .
the Foodwatch consumer organisation , which has a working paper from the EU , strongly criticised the plans : &quot; risks and side effects of failed industrial and environmental policies are passed on to pregnant women and young children , &quot; said Matthias Wolfschmidt of Foodwatch .
according to Wolfschmidt , the limit values of nerve poison for large fish at the end of the food chain , such as shark or swordfish , are to be increased from one to two milligrams of mercury per kilogram of fish .
however , large predators are already so heavily burdened with mercury that around 50 % of catches cannot be sold on the basis of the remaining limit values .
after doubling the limit values , only 14.5 % would be irretrievable .
in return for this easing , according to Foodwatch , the EU wants to tighten the limit values for other fish from 0.5 milligrams to 0.1 milligrams of mercury per kilogram .
Foodwatch , however , called this a &quot; trick &quot; because smaller graveyards , such as carp , are usually so low that they are already complying with the planned highs today .
thus , the reduction in cloning is &quot; a perfidious distraction that helps the economy alone , &quot; Wolfschmidt explained .
mercury is a highly toxic heavy metal for humans , which is highly enriched by the food chain , especially in predators .
the federal government therefore warns that &quot; already low levels of damage to the nervous system &quot; can cause .
however , the Federal Ministry of the Environment states on its homepage that there is no risk to public health .
mercury comes into the environment mainly through coal incineration .
according to a written statement from the Federal Ministry of the Environment , Germany &apos;s coal @-@ fired power plants are producing more than six tonnes of mercury a year , two thirds of the total quantity emitted in Germany .
the concentration of mercury in fish , for example , in Elbe , Rhine and Danube , was &quot; permanently and nationally exceeded , &quot; the &quot; Spiegel &quot; quoted from the paper in March .
last year , Europe @-@ wide warnings about mercury in fish were already among the most frequently reported health risks in the EU &apos;s RASFF alert system .
Foodwatch calls on consumers to protest against the EU &apos;s plans at : www.mercury @-@ action.foodwatch.de
